commentary: Taskin Ahmed to Latham, SIX runs century comes with a clean hit over deep midwicket. It was short and Latham was waiting for it. Picks the length early, gets into a nice position and pulls it clean over deep midwicket. Second ODI century for Latham. Proud moment for dad Rod Latham, who is present at the venue. Soaks in a warm ovation from his hometown crowd

commentary: Ferguson to Tamim Iqbal, 4 leg byes ooh, lucky boundary. That was a superb short ball, had Tamim scampering for cover. Might have been undone by the pace as well as the ball goes off the glove and a part of the helmet as well over the keeper and the cordon

commentary: Santner to Mashrafe Mortaza, OUT makes room for himself but Santner follows him and Mortaza is cramped for room. He is not able to free his arms as well as he would have liked and his wild slog only carries till the fielder at deep midwicket. And Mortaza's burst meets a swift end
